</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="617" type="breeding">
<paragraph blockId="22.[145,1350,1321,2025]" pageId="22" pageNumber="617">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[147,281,1754,1787]" pageId="22" pageNumber="617">Breeding.</emphasis>
Two pregnant Kano’s Moles were collected in August and March, each with three fetuses.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[145,726,1838,1867]" pageId="22" pageNumber="617" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="22.[145,1350,1321,2025]" box="[145,726,1838,1867]" pageId="22" pageNumber="617">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[145,380,1838,1867]" pageId="22" pageNumber="617">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Kano’s Mole is fossorial.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
